<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n35213e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35213e">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35213e"> 213(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> multazam / breast pressed / against house / prayer</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Thus the space of ten spans between the black stone and the door <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> is called the <i>Multazam</i>, and here prayer should be offered after the tawaf with outstretched arms and breast pressed against the house. <small> &ldquo;MECCA&rdquo; <a name="EBMC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBMC"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 953</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
